<knowl mode="exercise" xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
    <knowl>
        <content>
            <list>
                <item><p>Write an equation (in <em>standard form</em>), and</p></item>
                <item><p>sketch a picture</p></item>
            </list>
            <p>
for the circle with 
center <m>{{center}}</m> and 
radius <m> {{radius}} </m>.
            </p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <list>
                <item>
                <p>
<m>\displaystyle \left({{DeltaX}}\right)^2 + \left({{DeltaY}}\right)^2 = {{radius^2}}</m>
                </p>
                </item>
                <item>
                <p>The image of the circle:</p>
<p><image
    source="assets/PBL2/generated/{{__seed__}}/Show1.png"
    description="a red circle with given radius and blue center point"
/></p>
                <p>Check the scale on the <m>x</m> and <m>y</m>
                axes to verify the center and radius are correct.</p>
                </item>
            </list>
        </outtro>
    </knowl>

    <knowl>
        <content>
            <p>
For the circle depicted below, write equations which define
            </p>
            <list>
                <item><p>the entire circle (in <em>standard form</em>);</p></item>
                <item><p>only the {{half}} half of the circle in the form
                    <m>y = f(x)</m> for some function <m>f(x)</m>.</p></item>
            </list>
            <p>
(Assume that the coordinates of the center and 
the length of the radius are all integer values.)
            </p>
<p><image
    source="assets/PBL2/generated/{{__seed__}}/Show2.png"
    description="a red circle with a blue center point"
/></p>            
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <list>
                <item>
                    <p>
<m> \displaystyle \left( {{dx}} \right)^2 + \left( {{dy}} \right)^2 = {{rsq}} </m>
                    </p>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <p>
<m> \displaystyle y = {{yc}}  {{pm}}  \sqrt{ {{rsq}} - \left( {{dx}} \right)^2 } </m>;
i.e., <m> f(x) = {{yc}}  {{pm}}  \sqrt{ {{rsq}} - \left( {{dx}} \right)^2 } </m>
                    </p>
                </item>
            </list>
        </outtro>
    </knowl>
</knowl>